Instruction: With all modules connected and switches ON, use a multimeter referenced to the power supply negative terminal. Probe each node along the series path: power supply positive output, then the two terminals of control module 1 (input pair), then its output pair, then into control module 2, and so on up to the input of the load module. At each point, record whether the voltage is ~+12 V, ~0 V, or floating/undefined. Do not disconnect any cables; just back‑probe or use accessible test points inside each module.
