description: With all modules connected and switches ON, use a multimeter referenced to the power supply negative terminal. Probe each node along the series path: power supply positive output, then the two terminals of control module 1 (input pair), then its output pair, then into control module 2, and so on up to the input of the load module. At each point, record whether the voltage is ~+12 V, ~0 V, or floating/undefined. Do not disconnect any cables; just back‑probe or use accessible test points inside each module., outcome='PSU Output Cable (+) through Control Output Cable (+) 5 all measure ~+12 V on their (+) conductors and 0 V on their (−) conductors, with no polarity inversions detected. At Control Input Cable (+) 6, the (+) side is still at ~+12 V, but from Control Output Cable 6 onward (including all subsequent control modules and the load input cables), both (+) and (−) conductors measure 0 V.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=700.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control module 6 cabling / series link to Control module 7,
description: With power OFF, disconnect both cable pairs between Control module 6 and Control module 7. Using a continuity tester or multimeter in ohms mode, identify which two terminals on Control module 6 are internally connected straight through (the series path), and similarly on Control module 7. Then, still with power off, verify that the cable pairs are connected such that each module’s high (12 V) through‑conductor goes to the next module’s high through‑conductor and each low (0 V) through‑conductor goes to the next module’s low through‑conductor. Report whether any cross‑connection or mis‑pairing is found between modules 6 and 7., outcome='Between Control modules 6 and 7, the (+) through‑conductor is continuous from Control Output Cable (+) 6 to Control Input Cable (+) 7, and the (−) through‑conductor is continuous from Control Output Cable (−) 6 to Control Input Cable (−) 7, with no cross‑connection between + and −. No POLARITY INVERSION DETECTED between the tested cables.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=380.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_continuity', 20.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> cabling / series link between Control module 7 and Control module 8 (and onward to Load module),
description: With power OFF, disconnect the cable pairs between Control module 7 and Control module 8, and between Control module 8 and the Load module. Using a continuity tester or multimeter in ohms mode, determine for Control modules 7 and 8 which two terminals are the straight-through series conductors (high and low). Then verify that the cable pairs are connected so that each module’s high (12 V) through‑conductor goes to the next module’s high through‑conductor and each low (0 V) through‑conductor goes to the next module’s low through‑conductor, up to the load module. Report any cross‑connection, swapped pair, or open circuit found on these links., outcome='All individual control and load cables tested show nominal continuity (~0.10 Ω).  \nPoint-to-point checks confirm low-resistance (short) paths from Control Module 7 outputs to Control Module 8 inputs, and from Control Module 8 outputs to the load inputs, with no cross-connections, swapped pairs, or opens reported.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=320.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control module 6 internal circuit (switch path and indicator branch),
description: With power ON and all modules connected as originally, open the inspection panel of Control module 6. Using the supply negative as reference, measure the voltage at: (1) the module 6 input high terminal, (2) the node on the switch side that feeds the output high terminal, (3) the output high terminal, and (4) both ends of the indicator LED/resistor branch. Then, with power OFF, measure resistance between the input high and output high terminals (with switch ON) and between the input low and output low terminals, to confirm that the series path inside module 6 is intact. Report all measured voltages and resistances., outcome='Measured voltages (referenced to supply negative): Control Input Cable (+) 6 is at 11.9893 V; Control Switch 6 reads 0.0 V at both terminals; Control Output Cable (+) 6 reads 0.0 V at both terminals. The Power Flow Indicator (green) 6 and its series resistor are physically missing and cannot be measured. Continuity: Control Input Cable (+) 6 and Control Input Cable (−) 6 both measure 0.10 Ω (nominal), but the (+) cable’s port ‘n’ is floating/disconnected from the circuit.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=145.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
